headline: IBM (IBM) Is Up 6.7% After Quantum Bond Trading Breakthrough With HSBC – Has the Bull Case Changed?
summary: HSBC recently announced it conducted the world's first successful trial of quantum-enabled algorithmic bond trading using IBM's Heron quantum processors, achieving a significant improvement in trade outcome predictions over traditional computing methods.
